  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, what presence of mind to write a letter like that to me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so I thought, you know, life is great, because they never complained.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then I got a letter from my father dated August 9th, 1942, in which he said tomorrow, I'm going to be deported to an unknown destination and it may be a very long time before you hear from me again.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then I received a letter from my mother, dated September 1st, 1942, in which she makes reference to the fact that my father was-- had been deported and that she did not know where he was and had not heard from him, and that she was not deported at the same time as my father was, because he lately had been a forced laborer, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] but that now there was another transport leaving the following day and that she was leaving on that transport and that she was hoping to be reunited with my father somewhere, somehow, and that they would then carry their burden or their life.",
      "word_count": 112
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that was perhaps the first time that she was complaining with dignity and with courage, and she's asking me to be always honest, to be brave and good, to carry my head high, and to never forget them and to never forget any of all of us.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] then there was one more postcard from my mother, dated September 4, 1942, which I suspect was written on the train or whatever other mode of transportation that she was on.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I suspect she probably tossed it out and some kind soul picked it up and mailed it to me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it was written in real shaky handwriting.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
